<DESCRIPTION>RULE 2.4 ANNOUNCEMENT
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Rule 2.4 Announcement</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">NOT FOR RELEASE, PUBLICATION OR DISTRIBUTION, IN WHOLE OR IN PART, IN, INTO OR FROM ANY JURISDICTION WHERE TO DO SO WOULD CONSTITUTE A VIOLATION OF THE RELEVANT LAWS OF THAT JURISDICTION </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>This announcement does not constitute an announcement of a firm intention to make an offer under Rule 2.5 of the Takeover Code </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">7&nbsp;September 2009 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>KRAFT FOODS INC.
PROPOSES COMBINATION WITH CADBURY PLC, BUILDING </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ON A GLOBAL POWERHOUSE IN SNACKS, CONFECTIONERY AND QUICK </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>MEALS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Inc. (&#147;Kraft Foods&#148;)
today announces that it has made a proposal to the Board of Cadbury plc (&#147;Cadbury&#148;) to combine the two companies. The Board of Cadbury has rejected this proposal. Kraft Foods is committed to working toward a recommended transaction and to
maintaining a constructive dialogue and is announcing this proposal as a means to encourage and further that process. Included in Appendix I are two letters to the Chairman of Cadbury which set out the strong strategic rationale for the proposed
combination and the attractive premium and compelling value proposition for Cadbury&#146;s shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods is proposing an offer for Cadbury
(the &#147;Possible Offer&#148;) of 300 pence in cash and 0.2589 new Kraft Foods shares per Cadbury share. This values each Cadbury share at 745 pence (based on the closing price of $28.10 for a Kraft Foods share on 4&nbsp;September 2009 and an
exchange rate of 1.6346 $/&pound;) and values the entire issued share capital of Cadbury at &pound;10.2 billion. The combination would build on Kraft Foods&#146; position as a global powerhouse in snacks, confectionery and quick meals with a rich
portfolio of iconic brands. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Possible Offer represents a premium of: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">42% over Cadbury&#146;s share price of 524 pence on 3&nbsp;July 2009, prior to recent analyst suggestions regarding potential sector consolidation;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">34% over Cadbury&#146;s 90-day average share price of 555 pence in the period up to 4&nbsp;September 2009, the last business day preceding this announcement; and
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">31% over Cadbury&#146;s closing share price of 568 pence on 4&nbsp;September 2009, the last business day preceding this announcement. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods would also offer a mix and match facility under which Cadbury shareholders could elect, subject to
availability, to vary the proportions in which they would receive cash and new Kraft Foods shares. Kraft Foods reserves the right to change the terms of the Possible Offer and the consideration mix in the future as explained in the Important Notice
below. Financing would be on the basis that Kraft Foods would maintain an investment-grade credit rating. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods believes that the strategic and
financial rationale for the transaction is compelling. The transaction would create: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a company with approximately $50 billion in revenues; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a global powerhouse in snacks, confectionery and quick meals, with an exceptional portfolio of leading brands around the world; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a geographically diversified combined business, with leading positions and significant scale in key developing markets including India, Mexico, Brazil, China and
Russia; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a strong presence in instant consumption channels in both developed and developing markets, expanding the reach and margin potential of the combined business;* and
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">the potential for meaningful revenue synergies over time from investments in distribution, marketing and product development. In addition, there is a significant
opportunity to realise pre-tax cost savings of at least $625 million annually. This is expected to be achieved through increased operational efficiencies over and above the current performance improvement programmes at Kraft Foods and Cadbury
(including Cadbury&#146;s Vision Into Action (&#147;VIA&#148;) programme). Kraft Foods expects that it will achieve the run-rate on these cost savings by the end of the third year following completion. Total one-off implementation cash costs of
approximately $1.2 billion would be incurred in the first three years following completion.** </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods has a proven track record of
successfully completing and integrating strategic combinations to build iconic brands and multi-national businesses, including the acquisitions of LU in 2007 and Nabisco in 2000. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In addition, Kraft Foods expects that the combination would enhance its growth and margin profile, and be accretive to earnings in the second year following completion on a cash basis </FONT>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(which excludes the one-time expenses related to the transaction and the impact of non-cash items such as the amortisation of intangibles after
acquisition).* Should the combination with Cadbury be completed, Kraft Foods would expect to revise its long-term growth targets to 5+% for revenue and 9-11% for earnings per share, from its previously announced 4+% and 7-9% respectively.*
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Commenting on the proposed transaction, Irene B. Rosenfeld, Chairman and CEO of Kraft Foods, said: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;This proposed combination is about growth. We are eager to build upon Cadbury&#146;s iconic brands and strong British heritage through increased investment and
innovation. We have great respect and admiration for Cadbury, its employees, its leadership and its proud heritage. As we have done, Cadbury has built wonderful brands by focusing on quality, innovation and marketing, but we believe the next stage
in Cadbury&#146;s development will be challenging, given the increased importance of scale in the industry. Cadbury&#146;s brands, which are highly complementary to our portfolio, would benefit from Kraft Foods&#146; global scope and scale and array
of proprietary technologies and processes. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Our extensive combined global business network would create opportunities for talented Cadbury employees
and managers across all areas of the combined enterprise. We would augment Kraft Foods&#146; and Cadbury&#146;s world-class capabilities by employing a &#145;best of both&#146; focus, from sales and marketing to distribution and manufacturing.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Our current plans contemplate that the UK would be a net beneficiary in terms of jobs. For example, we believe we would be in a position to continue
to operate the Somerdale facility, which is currently planned to be closed, and to invest in Bournville, thereby preserving UK manufacturing jobs. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">&#147;We have taken note of Cadbury&#146;s recent performance and the ongoing implementation of its VIA programme. We believe that Cadbury&#146;s share price already reflects its prospects as a standalone entity and the benefits of VIA. Our
proposal therefore not only takes into account these factors, but also provides a compelling premium and, we believe, significantly more value for Cadbury shareholders than Cadbury could create independently. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;We hope to engage with the Board of Cadbury on a constructive basis with the goal of consummating a recommended
transaction.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Further information on Kraft Foods </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Kraft Foods (NYSE: KFT, www.kraftfoodscompany.com) is the world&#146;s second largest food company with annual revenues of $42 billion. For many years, Kraft Foods has been growing and developing well-loved brands, including: Terry&#146;s,
Milka, C&ocirc;te d&#146;Or and Toblerone chocolates; Oreo, Ritz and LU biscuits; Kenco, Maxwell House, Carte Noire and Jacobs coffees; and Dairylea and Philadelphia cheeses. Headquartered in Northfield, Illinois, USA, Kraft Foods employs
approximately 100,000 people worldwide. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For further information on Kraft Foods, please go to www.transactioninfo.com/kraftfoods </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Important notice </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Possible Offer is subject to the following
pre-conditions: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(i)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods being granted access to conduct and complete satisfactory, limited, confirmatory due diligence; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(ii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods obtaining satisfactory financing; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">the unanimous recommendation of the Board of Cadbury. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods
reserves the right to: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(i)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">make an offer at any time at a value below the equivalent of 300 pence in cash and 0.2589 of new Kraft Foods shares per Cadbury share (taking the value of a Kraft Foods share and
the exchange rate at the date of announcement of a firm intention to make an offer) with the agreement and recommendation of the Board of Cadbury or in the event that any Cadbury dividend is declared, made or paid (other than the announced interim
dividend of 5.7 pence due to be paid by Cadbury on 16&nbsp;October 2009); </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(ii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">vary the form and/or mix of consideration of the Possible Offer as set out above; and/or </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">waive any or all of the pre-conditions to the making of an offer referred to above. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Lazard is acting as lead financial adviser to Kraft Foods. Centerview Partners, Citigroup and Deutsche Bank are also
acting as financial advisers. Citigroup and Deutsche Bank are acting as corporate brokers to Kraft Foods. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>This announcement does not constitute an
announcement of a firm intention to make an offer under Rule 2.5 of the Takeover Code and, accordingly, shareholders are advised that there can be no certainty that any offer to acquire Cadbury shares will be made even if the pre-conditions are
satisfied. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">* Nothing in this announcement is intended to be a profit forecast and the statements in this announcement should not be interpreted to
mean that the earnings per Kraft Foods share for the current or future financial periods will necessarily be greater than those for the relevant preceding financial period. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">** There are several material assumptions underlying the cost savings estimate which might therefore be materially greater or less than that estimated. This estimate of cost savings has been reported on under the
Takeover Code by Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP and by Lazard&nbsp;&amp; Co., Limited. Copies of their letters are included in parts (a)&nbsp;and (b)&nbsp;respectively of Appendix III. The estimate of cost savings should be read in conjunction with
Appendix II, which contains, among other information, certain key assumptions underlying the estimate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Enquiries: </U></B></FONT></P> <P

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Rule 2.10 disclosure </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Kraft Foods announces, in accordance with Rule 2.10 of the UK City Code on Takeovers and Mergers (the &#147;Takeover Code&#148;), that at the close of business on 4&nbsp;September 2009, Kraft Foods had the following relevant securities
(within the meaning of the Takeover Code) in issue: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1,475,768,518 shares (excluding shares held in Treasury). The ISIN reference number for these
securities is US50075N1046. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Further information </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This
announcement will be available on Kraft Foods&#146; website (www.kraftfoodscompany.com) by no later than 12 noon (London time) on 8&nbsp;September 2009. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Lazard&nbsp;&amp; Co., Limited, which is authorised and regulated in the United Kingdom by the Financial Services Authority, is acting as financial adviser to Kraft Foods and no one else in connection with the contents of this announcement
and the Possible Offer and will not be responsible to any person other than Kraft Foods for providing the protections afforded to clients of Lazard&nbsp;&amp; Co., Limited, nor for providing advice in relation to the Possible Offer or any matters
referred to herein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Centerview Partners LLC, whose United Kingdom business is authorised and regulated in the United Kingdom by the Financial Services
Authority, is acting as financial adviser to Kraft Foods and no one else in connection with the contents of this announcement and the Possible Offer and will not be responsible to any person other than Kraft Foods for providing the protections
afforded to clients of Centerview Partners LLC, nor for providing advice in relation to the Possible Offer or any matters referred to herein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Citigroup
Global Markets Limited, which is authorised and regulated in the United Kingdom by the Financial Services Authority, is acting as financial adviser and corporate broker to Kraft Foods and no one else in connection with the contents of this
announcement and the Possible Offer and will not be responsible to any person other than Kraft Foods for providing the protections afforded to clients of Citigroup Global Markets Limited, nor for providing advice in relation to the Possible Offer or
any matters referred to herein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Deutsche Bank AG is authorised under German Banking Law (competent authority: BaFin - Federal Financial Supervisory

providing the protections afforded to the clients of Deutsche Bank AG or the clients of Deutsche Bank Securities Inc. nor for providing advice in relation to the Possible Offer or any other matter referred to herein. </FONT></P> <P

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This announcement is not intended to, and does not, constitute or form part of any offer, invitation or the solicitation
of an offer to purchase, otherwise acquire, subscribe for, sell or otherwise dispose of, any securities, or the solicitation of any vote or approval in any jurisdiction, pursuant to this announcement or otherwise. Any offer will be made solely by
certain offer documentation which will contain the full terms and conditions of any offer, including details of how it may be accepted. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This announcement
has been prepared in accordance with English law and the Takeover Code and information disclosed may not be the same as that which would have been prepared in accordance with the laws of jurisdictions outside England. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The distribution of this announcement in jurisdictions other than the United Kingdom and the availability of the Possible Offer to shareholders of Cadbury who are not
resident in the United Kingdom may be affected by the laws of relevant jurisdictions. Therefore any persons who are subject to the laws of any jurisdiction other than the United Kingdom or shareholders of Cadbury who are not resident in the United
Kingdom will need to inform themselves about, and observe, any applicable requirements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">It is Kraft Foods&#146; preference to implement any offer by means
of a scheme of arrangement but Kraft Foods reserves the right to change this to a general offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Forward-looking statements </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This announcement contains forward-looking statements regarding Kraft Foods&#146; Possible Offer to combine with Cadbury, expected future earnings, revenues, cost
savings, operations, business trends and other such items, based on Kraft Foods&#146; plans, estimates and projections. These forward-looking statements involve risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from those
predicted in any such forward-looking statements. Such factors, include, but are not limited to, the possibility that the Possible Offer will not be pursued, failure to obtain necessary regulatory approvals or required financing or to satisfy any of
the other conditions to the combination, adverse effects on the market price of Kraft Foods&#146; common stock and on Kraft Foods&#146; operating results because of a failure to complete the combination, failure to realise the expected benefits of
the combination, negative effects of announcement or consummation of the combination on the market price of Kraft Foods&#146; common stock, significant transaction costs and/or unknown liabilities and general economic and business conditions that
affect the combined companies following the combination. For additional information on these and other factors that could affect Kraft Foods&#146; forward-looking statements, see Kraft Foods&#146; filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;), including Kraft Foods&#146; most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K and subsequent reports on Forms 10-Q and 8-K. Kraft Foods disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any
forward-looking statement in this announcement except as required by applicable law or regulation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Additional U.S.-related information </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This announcement is provided for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Cadbury or Kraft
Foods. Subject to future developments, Kraft Foods may file a </FONT>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">8 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">registration statement and/or tender offer documents with the SEC in connection with the proposed combination. <B>Cadbury shareholders should read those
filings, and any other filings made by Kraft Foods with the SEC in connection with the combination, as they will contain important information.</B> Those documents, if and when filed, as well as Kraft Foods&#146; other public filings with the SEC
may be obtained without charge at the SEC&#146;s website at www.sec.gov and at Kraft Foods&#146; website at www.kraftfoodscompany.com. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Dealing
disclosure requirements </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under the provisions of Rule 8.3 of the Takeover Code, if any person is, or becomes, &#147;interested&#148; (directly or
indirectly) in 1% or more of any class of &#147;relevant securities&#148; of Kraft Foods or of Cadbury, all &#147;dealings&#148; in any &#147;relevant securities&#148; of that company (including by means of an option in respect of, or a derivative
referenced to, any such &#147;relevant securities&#148;) must be publicly disclosed by no later than 3.30 pm (London time) on the London business day following the date of the relevant transaction. This requirement will continue until the date on
which the offer becomes, or is declared, unconditional as to acceptances, lapses or is otherwise withdrawn or on which the &#147;offer period&#148; otherwise ends. If two or more persons act together pursuant to an agreement or understanding,
whether formal or informal, to acquire an &#147;interest&#148; in &#147;relevant securities&#148; of Kraft Foods or of Cadbury, they will be deemed to be a single person for the purpose of Rule 8.3. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under the provisions of Rule 8.1 of the Takeover Code, all &#147;dealings&#148; in &#147;relevant securities&#148; of Kraft Foods or of Cadbury by Kraft Foods or
Cadbury, or by any of their respective &#147;associates&#148;, must be disclosed by no later than 12.00 noon (London time) on the London business day following the date of the relevant transaction. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A disclosure table, giving details of the companies in whose &#147;relevant securities&#148; &#147;dealings&#148; should be disclosed, and the number of such securities
in issue, can be found on the Takeover Panel&#146;s website at www.thetakeoverpanel.org.uk. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Interests in securities&#148; arise, in summary, when a
person has long economic exposure, whether conditional or absolute, to changes in the price of securities. In particular, a person will be treated as having an &#147;interest&#148; by virtue of the ownership or control of securities, or by virtue of
any option in respect of, or derivative referenced to, securities. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Terms in quotation marks are defined in the Takeover Code, which can also be found on
the Takeover Panel&#146;s website. If you are in any doubt as to whether or not you are required to disclose a &#147;dealing&#148; under Rule 8, you should consult the Takeover Panel. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

SIZE="1">Chairman&nbsp;&amp; Chief Executive Officer </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">28&nbsp;August 2009 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;R. Carr </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Cadbury plc </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Cadbury House </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sanderson Road </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Uxbridge </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">UB8 1DH </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Roger, </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I very much enjoyed meeting you this morning. As I explained, we believe that the combination of our companies would provide a compelling value proposition for both our
shareholders. As analysts and industry observers have long speculated, our two great companies are highly complementary and a combination makes a great deal of strategic and financial sense. We believe that now is the time to pursue a transaction as
a result of the significant opportunities available to both of us. We look forward to engaging in constructive, friendly discussions and working toward a positive outcome on a recommended basis. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have great respect and admiration for Cadbury plc (&#147;Cadbury&#148;), its employees, its leadership and its proud heritage. We have also taken note of your recent
performance and the successful ongoing implementation of your Vision Into Action programme. However, we believe that Cadbury&#146;s prospects, ability to fully realise operational efficiencies and capacity to invest are necessarily constrained given
its limited scale and scope relative to larger global competitors. We see few catalysts for sustained future value creation for Cadbury as a standalone entity. In contrast, we have concluded that we can strengthen both our companies by bringing them
together, enhancing our worldwide scale and scope, and capitalising on significant opportunities to build a global leader in the food and snacking industry for the benefit of all of our respective stakeholders. In so doing, we are eager to build
upon the success of your iconic brands and strong British heritage through increased investment and innovation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Accordingly, I am writing to set out the
details of a possible offer to combine Cadbury and Kraft Foods Inc. (&#147;Kraft Foods&#148;) (a &#147;Possible Offer&#148;), as approved by the Board of Directors of Kraft Foods. Subject to the pre-conditions set out below, Kraft Foods is prepared
to offer 300 pence in cash and 0.2589 new Kraft Foods shares per Cadbury share, which values each Cadbury share at 755 pence (based on yesterday&#146;s closing price of $28.42 for a Kraft Foods share and an exchange rate of 1.617 $/&pound;). This
price represents an attractive premium to any measure of the standalone value of Cadbury and fully reflects your recent performance and prospects. Specifically, this price represents a premium of: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">44% over Cadbury&#146;s share price of 524 pence on 3&nbsp;July 2009, prior to recent analyst suggestions regarding potential sector consolidation;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">31% over Cadbury&#146;s share price of 578 pence at close yesterday. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We would also point out that this price is beyond any price at which Cadbury&#146;s shares have traded since the demerger. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">The Possible Offer would provide your shareholders with both value certainty and the opportunity to enjoy the significant value upside in the combined entity&#146;s attractive growth prospects and considerable synergies. Kraft Foods would
also offer a mix and match facility under which Cadbury shareholders could elect, subject to availability, to vary the proportions in which they would receive cash and new Kraft Foods shares. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I believe that the strategic and financial rationale for this transaction is compelling. The transaction would create: </FONT></P> <P

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">the potential for meaningful revenue synergies over time from investments in distribution, marketing and product development, as well as a significant opportunity
to realise pre-tax cost savings of at least $625 million annually through increased operational efficiencies</FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">1</SUP></FONT><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods has a proven track record of successfully completing and integrating strategic
combinations to build iconic brands and multi-national businesses, including the acquisitions of LU in 2007 and Nabisco in 2000. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A combination with
Cadbury is consistent with Kraft Foods&#146; stated strategic objective to build a high-performing global company by reframing our categories, capitalising on our established sales capabilities and driving down costs without compromising our
commitment to high quality. Over the past three years, we have successfully positioned Kraft Foods for sustainable, profitable growth. A combination with Cadbury would mark a logical next step in our transformation as we shape the company into a
more global, higher-growth and higher-margin entity. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Together, we would draw on the collective strengths of our two organisations and create a stronger,
more competitive global company for the benefit of all stakeholders. We believe that the growth prospects and global scope of the enlarged entity should lead to increased </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:8px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>

</FONT></TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">opportunities for talented employees and managers of both companies. In addition, we confirm that the existing
contractual employment rights, including pension rights, of all employees of Cadbury would be fully safeguarded. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The consideration required for the
Possible Offer would be provided from a combination of Kraft Foods&#146; existing funds, new debt and the issuance of equity. Financing would be on the basis that Kraft Foods would maintain an investment-grade credit rating. The significant cash
flow of the enlarged entity following a combination would allow for rapid debt paydown and the continued funding of growth initiatives. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We, together with
our legal advisers, have undertaken an analysis in relation to anti-trust matters. The complementary nature of our two businesses means that any antitrust concerns will be few, and limited in scope: we are confident that any issues can be
appropriately addressed within the envisaged implementation timeframe. In this regard, we would suggest that our respective legal advisers meet at your earliest convenience, in order for our advisers to explain their analysis, and for next steps to
be identified. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We believe it is in all parties&#146; interests to progress this transaction as swiftly as possible. Our senior management and advisers
have already completed extensive analysis and due diligence based on publicly available information. Accordingly, our due diligence requirements are limited, confirmatory in nature and capable of being addressed within a compressed timeframe. Lazard
is acting as our lead financial adviser. We have also retained Centerview Partners, Citigroup and Deutsche Bank as financial advisers. Our legal advisers are Clifford Chance; Cravath, Swaine&nbsp;&amp; Moore; Gibson, Dunn&nbsp;&amp; Crutcher; and
Arnold&nbsp;&amp; Porter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">It is Kraft Foods&#146; preference to implement any offer by means of a scheme of arrangement but we reserve the right to change
this to a general offer. Any offer, if made, would be subject to the terms and conditions usually attaching to a scheme of arrangement, or offer, involving a UK public company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The making of any offer would be subject to the following pre-conditions: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

proposal in an expeditious manner. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Per our conversation, I look forward to hearing from you shortly. </FONT></P> <P

SIZE="1">Chairman&nbsp;&amp; Chief Executive Officer </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">7&nbsp;September 2009 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;R. Carr </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Cadbury plc </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Cadbury House </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sanderson Road </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Uxbridge </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">UB8 1DH </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Roger, </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Thank you for your letter in response to our discussion on 28&nbsp;August and the letter I sent to you as a follow-up outlining our possible offer (a &#147;Possible
Offer&#148;) for Cadbury plc (&#147;Cadbury&#148;). I have given careful consideration to your response. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Although I am disappointed that you rejected
unequivocally our proposal, I remain committed to working toward a recommended offer and to maintaining a constructive dialogue. We are therefore disclosing publicly our Possible Offer as a means to encourage and further that process. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I continue to believe strongly in the strategic rationale for combining our two companies and that our Possible Offer represents an attractive premium and a compelling
value proposition for your shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As I outlined during our meeting, I believe we can strengthen both of our companies by bringing them together,
enhancing their worldwide scale and scope, and capitalising on significant opportunities, building on the position of Kraft Foods Inc. (&#147;Kraft Foods&#148;) as a global powerhouse in snacks, confectionery and quick meals for the benefit of all
of our respective stakeholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We understand the great sense of pride that you and your team have for Cadbury and its brands. We also have a long history
of respecting and building iconic brands like Oreo, LU, Milka, Toblerone, Kenco, Philadelphia and Dairylea to name just a few. Kraft Foods is committed to building upon Cadbury&#146;s success and strong British heritage through increased investment
and innovation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our extensive combined global business network would create opportunities for talented Cadbury employees and managers across all areas of
the combined enterprise. We would augment Kraft Foods&#146; and Cadbury&#146;s world-class capabilities by employing a &#147;best of both&#148; focus, from sales and marketing to distribution and manufacturing. For example, we believe we would be in
a position to continue to operate the Somerdale facility, which is currently planned to be closed, and invest in Bournville, thereby preserving UK manufacturing jobs. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">15 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I also want to reiterate that our Possible Offer represents a compelling value proposition for your shareholders. Given
the proposed consideration mix of cash and shares, they would enjoy both value certainty and significant potential upside in the combined entity&#146;s attractive growth prospects and meaningful synergies. As we discussed, and as I noted in my
previous letter to you, we commend you on your successful ongoing implementation of Vision Into Action (&#147;VIA&#148;). I believe Cadbury&#146;s share price already reflects its prospects as a standalone entity and the benefits of VIA. Our
Possible Offer therefore not only takes into account these factors, but also provides a significant premium and, I believe, significantly more value for your shareholders than Cadbury could create independently. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Together, we can draw on the collective strengths of our two organisations to create a stronger, more competitive global company for the benefit of all our stakeholders.
I would ask you to reconsider your rejection of our Possible Offer and would welcome a constructive dialogue. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Yours sincerely, </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Irene B. Rosenfeld </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For the avoidance of doubt, this letter should not be
construed in any regard as constituting an offer or evincing an intention to make an offer or inviting an offer or imposing an obligation to make an offer for Cadbury and any of its securities or otherwise giving rise to legal relations and, in
particular, does not constitute a firm intention to make an offer for the purposes of Rule 2.5 of The City Code on Takeovers and Mergers. This letter shall be governed by and construed in accordance with English law. </FONT></P> <P

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>APPENDIX II: SOURCES AND BASES </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Unless otherwise stated, financial and other information concerning Cadbury and Kraft Foods has been extracted from published sources or from Kraft Foods&#146; management sources.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The expected sources of the stated expected annual pre-tax cost savings of at least $625 million are: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential operational cost savings of $300 million per annum resulting from efficiencies and economies of scale in the areas of procurement, manufacturing, customer service,
logistics and research and development; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">17 </FONT></P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential general and administrative cost savings of $200 million resulting from efficiencies in the areas of central, regional and country level administrative expenses; and
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential marketing and selling cost savings of $125 million resulting from efficiencies and economies of scale in the areas of marketing, media and selling expenses.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">When evaluating the cost savings the Board of Kraft Foods has assumed the following: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">that Kraft Foods will acquire 100% of the shares in Cadbury following completion, without undue delay; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">that there will be no material unanticipated impact on the combined group arising from any decisions made by competition authorities; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">that there will be no material change to the market dynamics affecting Kraft Foods and/or Cadbury following completion; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">that there will be no material change to exchange rates following completion. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In establishing the estimate of cost savings, the Board of Kraft Foods has assumed that Cadbury&#146;s operations, processes and procedures are comparable to those of Kraft
Foods&#146; own related operations, except where publicly available information clearly indicates otherwise. Kraft Foods&#146; management, aided by its previous integration experience and through an understanding of Cadbury&#146;s cost structure
based on their own market intelligence and experience, has determined the source and scale of realisable cost savings. The cost savings and the one-off implementation cash costs of achieving the cost savings are incremental to Kraft Foods&#146; and,
to the best of the Directors and Executive Officers of Kraft Foods&#146; knowledge, Cadbury&#146;s existing plans. In addition to information from Kraft Foods&#146; management, the sources of information that Kraft Foods has used to arrive at the
estimate of cost savings include: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>KRAFT FOODS INC. (&#147;KRAFT FOODS&#148;)&#146;S PROPOSAL TO CADBURY PLC (&#147;CADBURY&#148;) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Sirs </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We refer to the statements (the &#147;Statements&#148;) Kraft
Foods set out on page 2 and in Appendix II, clause (h)&nbsp;of the announcement dated 7&nbsp;September 2009 (the &#147;Announcement&#148;), to the effect that: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;The transaction would create&#133; a significant opportunity to realise pre-tax cost savings of at least $625 million annually. This is expected to be achieved through increased operational efficiencies over and
above the current performance improvement programmes at Kraft Foods and Cadbury (including Cadbury&#146;s Vision Into Action (&#147;VIA&#148;) programme). Kraft Foods expects that it will achieve the run-rate on these cost savings by the end of the
third year following completion. Total one-off implementation cash costs of approximately $1.2 billion would be incurred in the first three years following completion&#148;; and </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;The expected sources of the stated expected annual pre-tax cost savings of at least $625 million are: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(i)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential operational cost savings of $300 million per annum resulting from efficiencies and economies of scale in the areas of procurement, manufacturing, customer service,
logistics and research and development; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(ii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential general and administrative cost savings of $200 million resulting from efficiencies in the areas of central, regional and country level administrative expenses; and
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">potential marketing and selling cost savings of $125 million resulting from efficiencies and economies of scale in the areas of marketing, media and selling expenses.&#148;
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">21 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">

<IMG SRC="g85780g37v12.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Statements have been made in the context of disclosures in Appendix II of the Announcement setting out the basis of the
belief of the Directors and Executive Officers of Kraft Foods (the &#147;Directors&#148;) supporting the Statements and their analysis and explanation of the underlying constituent elements. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This letter is required by Note 8(b) of Rule 19.1 of the City Code on Takeovers and Mergers (the &#147;Takeover Code&#148;) and is given for the purpose of complying
with that requirement and for no other purpose. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Responsibility </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">The Directors are responsible for making the Statements in accordance with Rule 19.1 of the Takeover Code. It is our responsibility and that of Lazard&nbsp;&amp; Co., Limited (&#147;Lazard&#148;) to form our respective opinions, as required
by Note 8(b) to Rule 19.1 of the Takeover Code, as to whether the Statements have been made by the Directors with due care and consideration. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our work in
connection with the Statements has been undertaken solely for the purposes of reporting under Note 8(b) to Rule 19.1 of the Takeover Code to the Directors and to Lazard. We accept no responsibility to any other parties other than to those persons to
whom this report is expressly addressed in respect of, arising out of or in connection with that work. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our work has not been carried out in accordance
with auditing or other standards and practices generally accepted in other jurisdictions and accordingly should not be relied upon as if it had been carried out in accordance with those standards and practices. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Basis of opinion </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We conducted our work in accordance with the
Statements of Investment Circular Reporting Standard 1000 (Investment Reporting Standards applicable to all engagements in connection with an investment circular) issued by the Auditing Practices Board in the United Kingdom. We have discussed the
Statements together with the relevant bases of belief (including sources of information) with the Directors and with Lazard. Our work did not involve any independent examination of any of the financial or other information underlying the Statements.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We do not express any opinion as to the achievability of the cost savings and benefits identified in the Statements. The Statements are subject to
uncertainty as described in Appendix II to the Announcement. Because of the significant changes in the enlarged group&#146;s operations expected to flow from the proposed merger and because the Statements relate to the future, the actual benefits
achieved are likely to be different from those anticipated in the Statements and the differences may be material. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Opinion </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On the basis of the foregoing, we report that in our opinion the Directors have made the Statements, in the form and context in which they are made, with due care and
consideration. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Yours faithfully </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">

<IMG SRC="g85780g27d88.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<DESCRIPTION>MESSAGE TO STAKEHOLDERS
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Message to Stakeholders</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.2 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">

<IMG SRC="g85780g02j10.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>A MESSAGE TO STAKEHOLDERS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">As you know, on 7&nbsp;September 2009, Kraft Foods announced that we sent a letter to the Board of Directors of Cadbury plc to discuss the possibility of combining our two companies. Although the Board of Cadbury plc has rejected this
proposal, Kraft Foods is committed to working toward a recommended transaction and to maintaining a constructive dialogue. We believe that we can strengthen both our companies by bringing them together. We are eager to build upon Cadbury plc&#146;s
iconic brands and strong British heritage through increased investment and innovation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have great respect for Cadbury plc. We strongly believe that
combining our two well-respected companies is a great way for us both to continue to nurture and grow our collective brands. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This proposed combination
would create: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A company with approximately $50 billion in revenues; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A global powerhouse in snacks, confectionery and quick meals with an exceptional portfolio of leading brands; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A geographically diversified combined business, with leading positions and significant scale in key developing markets including India, Mexico, Brazil, China, and
Russia; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A strong presence in instant consumption channels in both developed and developing markets, expanding the reach and margin potential of the combined business.*
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We understand the great sense of pride that Cadbury plc has for its brands. Kraft Foods also has a long history of respecting and
building iconic brands like Oreo, LU, Milka, Toblerone, Kenco, Philadelphia and Dairylea. Kraft Foods is eager to build upon Cadbury plc&#146;s success, iconic brands and strong British heritage through increased investment and innovation.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We believe the business reasons for combining the two companies are clear, compelling and significant. But we believe this proposed combination is about
cultural &#147;fit&#148; as well. It&#146;s about value <I>and</I> values. We share many of the same priorities &#150; from food safety to sustainable sourcing to community involvement. In short, we see a great fit. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At this point, we have only made a proposal to combine our two companies. We have made no formal offer yet and there is no guarantee that we will make one. </FONT>
</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have asked the Board of Cadbury plc to consider our proposal with the hope of reaching an agreement. The timing of any potential transaction will depend
on a number of factors and we will make a further announcement when appropriate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Meanwhile, we invite you to visit our corporate website,
www.kraftfoodscompany.com, to learn more about our company. We will also update this transaction website with all of our latest communications about this proposed combination. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">*Nothing in this document is intended to be a profit forecast and the statements in this document should not be interpreted to mean that the earnings per Kraft Foods share for the current or future financial periods
will necessarily be greater than those for the relevant preceding financial period. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This document contains forward-looking statements regarding our possible offer to combine with Cadbury plc. Such statements include statements about the benefits of the
proposed combination, expected future earnings, revenues and cost savings and other such items, based on our plans, estimates and projections. These forward-looking statements involve risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ
materially from those predicted in any such forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, the possibility that the possible offer will not be pursued and the risk factors set forth in our filings with the US Securities
and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;), including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K and subsequent reports on Forms 10-Q and 8-K. We disclaim and do not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement
in this document except as required by applicable law or regulation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ADDITIONAL US-RELATED INFORMATION </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This document is provided for informational purposes only and is neither an offer to purchase nor a solicitation of an offer to sell shares of Cadbury plc or Kraft Foods.
Subject to future developments, Kraft Foods may file a registration statement and/or tender offer documents with the SEC in connection with the proposed combination. <B>Cadbury plc shareholders should read those filings, and any other filings made
by Kraft Foods with the SEC in connection with the proposed combination, as they will contain important information. </B>Those documents, if and when filed, as well as Kraft Foods&#146; other public filings with the SEC may be obtained without
charge at the SEC&#146;s website at <U>www.sec.gov</U> and at Kraft Foods&#146; website at <U>www.kraftfoodscompany.com</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>RESPONSIBILITY STATEMENT
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The directors of Kraft Foods each accept responsibility for the information contained in this document, save that the only responsibility accepted by
them in respect of information in this document relating to Cadbury plc or the Cadbury Group (which has been compiled from public sources) is to ensure that such information has been correctly and fairly reproduced and presented. Subject as
aforesaid, to the best of the knowledge and belief of the directors of Kraft Foods (who have taken all reasonable care to ensure that such is the case), the information contained in this document is in accordance with the facts and does not omit
anything likely to affect the import of that information. </FONT></P>
